items.text: Cheapest soya milk I had ever drink......30cents in a big cup.
Teochew fishball noodle is very nice
Jin ji coffee stall Kopi-o is nice.
Laksa is the bomb.
Stall #01-35 - bestest mee pok ever.
Veg stall cheap n yum yum
Fatt soon kueh is super super superrrre yummeh!
炎成潮州鱼圆面Blk 209 Hougang Street 21 #01-35 Kovan Market & Food Centre Open 7:30am to 10pm Rest on Mon. Fish Ball, Cai Yuan.
I love the fries from the western stall, Grill n Pasta at #01-41.
looking forward to opening soya bean stall
Hougang Hainanese Curry Rice is disappointing. Rice cooked with too little water and lor not fragrant.
The drinks stall 4SQ fans highlighted, that sells 30-cents bird's nest & soya drinks, is Sun Kee Drinks #01-65. Great thirst-quenching stuff on a hot day
Char siew stall

Bedok North 85's stall auntie is fucking stingy with her ingredients. She only put 2 oysters into the fried oyster. Want to be stingy then don't open a business.it will be my first and last time here.
Nice Chai Ji Fish soup! The fish is fresh!
Losta awards for this roasted meat.. Now I gonna see if this is still nice. Last ate 5yrs back
Carrot cake and chicken rice. Eat both at the same time :)
Nice! Stall pple are nice too! おいしい食べ物と親切な店員よ‼
A good example of a heartland hawker centre. Bright and airy, with decent standard of hawker fares. The corner coffee stall nearest to heartland mall is good.
A1 kway chap super salty. The mei cai salty ok. The sauce us salty, the soup with the kway is salty too. The serving of the kway is like half of what other stalls sell. Super not recommended.
Rojak: Kovan Rojak #01-39 serves one of the better offerings in the country. You have the option of adding more ingredients to this local fruit salad: toasted cuttlefish, century eggs & even abalone!
For fishball noodles, just zoom in on Yam Mee Teochew Fishball Mee #01-35. Don't waste ur calorie intake on other stalls :-P
30cents soya milk @ sunkee 01-65 come early cos sold out in afternoon
57 Yi Shi Jia Wanton Mee - in memorise of old school wanton mee of 70's
Mutton soup to warm up tummy.
Desert here damn nice.
Cheap and nice food. Especially the fish ball noodle .
many awesome foods here!!
Hajjah Mariam Muslim Food has the best Malay food here. Loves its nasi lemak, mee soto, lontong. Yum!!
Their pasta is horrible n overpriced
Thick soya bean drink at ONLY 30 cents!! #01-65. Just when I thought it's impossible to get anything below 50-cents!
Malay rice 3 dishes for $2. Cant believe it! 2 fishes, potato n beancurd
Wantan noodles: Yi Shi Jia #01-57 noodles had bitter aftertaste :-( Black sauce version was tasteless. Yuck!
2 best kopi stalls here, Yuan Ji Coffee Stall and San Xin Coffee Stall.
A1 Kway Chap. Highly recommended!
Do not patronise Feng Yuan Fresh Sugarcane Juice, #01-55 if u dun wanna to be cheated! !!$4.50 for only  "mountain" of colour ice with no sign of kiwi, strawberry and mango.
Chuan Heng cooked food Chee cheong fun is great.
Don't eat fish ball noodle at #01-05, I've got cheated by the queue. Eat at teochew fish ball noodle stall. It is the best! Yums.
Roasted Duck rice is the best here Bedok Cooked Food
發記鹵面very stingy on the gravy
Wantan Mee. 51 Mingfa #01-64 packs above average WTM. Noodles r 'q' (springy), wantans hv strong hints of pepper & char siew (BBQ pork) slices succulent. Super-long waiting time on weekends!
Birdnest drink @$0.30, price never change since 15 years ago
Must-tries: Teochew Meepok, Chicken Rice, Malay food, Kway Chap, Economic Beehoon. Perfect place for early morning breakfast too.
Fried kway tiao @ #01-30 is good
Egg wanton noodle, open till noon, closed on Monday's and tuesdays
The kopi here is one of the best I had in Singapore. Definitely will come back for the kopi.
Bedok North 85 Fried Oyster not nice at all! Oysters can't even be seen :(
jin ji teh o siew dai is the bomb! the auntie has a fiery temper, thou.
Pontian wanton noodles, need I to say any more?
Super yummy A1 kway chup! Love the chili, their fishcakes and the small intestines. Their duck meat is good too.
Here for the 春福鱼圆肉脞面。
鸡丝粥, youtiao & butterfly bun! 
Lots of good food.
Western food stall is value for money
Try Yam Mee.  Teochew Fishball Noodle & Laksa!!!
must try cheapest soya bean/chin chow drink in town!
51明发wanton egg noodle is the best!
Weng Huat carrot cake black is nice here! Must try!
Fresh fruit juice @ unit #01-22 Tian Cheng
#01-28 Congee is yummy!
Laksa and Chicken Curry Mee is a must try in one of the stalls, can't remember the number but it always has a long queue. :)
This is one of the few hawker centres that still sell good food for less than $3 per normal serving. Cheap & good!
Chicken rice must tryyy
Chicken rice is nice!
Nasi sambal goreng,lontong must try
Bad design of the hawker center, table 231 is dripping water when it rains! So disappointed, I travelled from west side
This hawker is very stuffy and hot.
I love the curry mixed vege rice!
金斩鸡 chicken rice is the best!!!!
Chinese Guo tie (pan fried) is very nice! A plate at $5 for 12 pcs
Bedok north 85 stall is over rated
Teochew mee pok...
A1 Kway Chup is so so only. Nothing to really to crow about. Zzz
Curry Chicken Noodle is a must have. #01-05. Look for the looooong queue.
If you are nearby, must come to this newly renovates hawker centre for some authentic local culinary delights.
The economical beehoon store is pricier than I thought. Egg, veg, fishcake & sausage beehoon costs me $4.70 & I thought it was $1.70. Sounds similar in Chinese..zzzZ I'd rather get . Pfft
Compact market area! Many shops around it, like McD, kovan mall-KFC, PizzaCorner, Cold Storage, Popular, NTUC, hardware key maker shops, CK, backers, and a 24hrs seaFood center.
Carrot cake stall at #01-13 facing carpark is nice.
Hokkien Mee @ Heng Heng cook food is best.
Teochew Kuehs at Xing Xing Cooked Food #01-11 are not bad.
Do not try e fish soup stalls in e back rolls without queue.. There's a reason why there's no queue... Sucks big time!
Soya bean here selling at 30cents ONLY!!!!Gd good!!!
Geylang Carrot Cake #01-13 is good...as always long queue...
The cheapest soya bean drink 30 cents only !!!!
发记 Teochew minced meat fishball noodle is a must try, esp during the evening shift taken over by the son. V nice big thank you after he serves you food. Nice portion of noodles as well. :)
Ist time in this market. Seems to have many good food stalls.  Minced pork n curry noodle is yummy.
Hussain Muslim Food has great value sets. $3 for a Sambal Ayam Goreng set or a Beef Rendang set.
Best Western food @Grill & Pasta #01-41.
Yi shi jia wanton mee (#01-57) with ketchup sauce da best!
Try the porridge beside Hup Lee nasi lemak stall! The uncle is very kind too :D
$2 carrot cake @ #01-58. Portion is big!
Yam Mee laksa. Yummy indeed!
Good food almost all stall.. problem might be finding a seat and table to be clean.
51 Ming huat wanton noodle must try
Sit around stall no. #01-57 for some really cool music!!! Nice!!!
The wanton mee is nice.  It's on the second level where the wet market is. You wouldn't miss the long queue.
財記fish soup - Tom Yam Instant Noodles fried fish so so. Noodles too soft
Don't go to Mei wei dessert. Dessert is so so and terrible attitude
Great kway chap!
Yam mee teochew fishball noodle is good.
Try the weng Huat carrot cake . Nice & tasty and affordable
The geyland fried carrot cake dem fucking expensive yet less.I fried $5 but it look like $2.swear no to visit tis stall anymore.85 bedok carrot cake look better.
Try Tong Fong fatt hainanese boneless chicken rice
Too many awesome foods here!!
There are 2 popular wanton noodle stalls in this hawker centre but I prefer 51 Ming Fa. Their noodle stands out; very springy, every bite is so yummy! Made my 40 minutes queue time well worth it.
Best Mee Tai Mak soup at #01-05. Must try..
Popiah and Muah Chee at stall #01-52
Recommend the curry rice . Round the corner
51明发wanton egg noodle is the best!!! Nice chilli !!
Try the Ming Huat Wanton Mee #01-64. Super nice!
Ok basically you've to try e porridge w e you tiao, pontian noodle, e veggie rice store, economical bee Hoon, fishball noodle, dessert and sugar cane!!!
The Hainanese curry rice beside the chicken rice store is fucking rude. Never buy from that store.
try e only vegetarian store here.. gt brown rice..
The carrot cake is the best in town.
Alot of choices here but which is the best...find ur seat before u order ur food
There is an unassuming stall Xing Xing 兴兴 near to the mutton soup that pan fry traditional teochew kuehs. The ku-chai kuehs are delicious!
Yes!! Is good 👍😊
Everything looks so yummy.
Geylang carrot cake is gd #01-13... Always long Q...
Curry rice the beat
porridge with youtiao! #01-28 
Love Pontian Wanton Noodles!
Try the noodle stalls , most of them are good
Chai tow kway. Pleasantly surprised that 85 Bedok North Fried Oyster #01-30 serves tasty CKT
Wantan mee at stall #01-64
Try A1 kway chap
Best fish soup in town!!!👍👍👍👍👍
Nasi lemak shiok
金斩chicken rice is fragrant and tender!
Bak Chor Mee: D long q @ stall #01-05 had me fantasising how delicious their minced meat fishball noodles was. It was an illusion. Noodle was starchy, rojak ingredients were fighting ea other :-(
發記fishball doesn't taste as good as it looks.
DIY popiah: Fortune Food #01-52 sells handmade (actually central kitchen) Popiah skin ($15/kg), ground peanuts, crispy bits, chilli sauce, etc to host ur own Popiah party @ home. They deliver too!

Chicken curry noodle: #01-05 was disappointing. Lotsa recommendations on 4SQ. After 15-min q later, realised it was just their laksa sauce with boiled chicken. Zero curry :-( I'll go Hong Lim nxt time
Postal box nearby. In front of the row of market stalls facing the bus interchange. These stalls r selling cloth, alteration svcs, handbags.
Mixed rice at #01-37 is a must try ;)  lotsa variety and the food definitely tastes good!!
A1 Kway Chap is only so-so. The best I had is still the one in Bedok.
Too many awesome foods here!!
Decent pasta selling at $5? Only seen here I think. Mama Pasta @ #01-52
tis yong tau hu stall beside the otah stall can try.. nt bad for $3.80.. like their prawn. n gt 1 tall girl at tis stall quite pretty.
Try the Chee Cheong fun (rice rolls) at stall facing wet market. Long q as lady owner slowly prepares each order. Delicious - smooth and yummy . Some say as good as those from KL.
kway chap stall (not A1) used to give one full egg per set, now only half egg. so giam for what, regulars like me know it is lesss, ok.
$0.30 Beancurd and Soya Bean Milk!! Amazing price! Soya bean milk so so only, but beancurd is super nice! Must try!! #01-65, Sun Kee Drinks! =)
Minced meat noodles.
Mee soto from Hajjah Mariam stall 
Great chicken rice at #01-19!
發記curry chicken Mee hoon Mee is excellent!
The malay rice is nice..
A1 is the best.. Must try the chicken rice & kway chap... Stall #01-15/16
51明发 wanton noodle's a rip off! $3 for so little!! The quality is OKAY though

Prawn noodles. Chai Kee #01-66 is the rare few stalls still serving kangkung (water spinach) AND taugeh (bean sprouts). Soup is clear & yummy. Lots of lar pok (fried pork lard cubes) for added flavour
Try 益食家云吞面... All time favorite
Cowboy Grill (#01-31) is not bad.
prawn mee, beside jinji coffee, is very nice. they use pork ribs as soup base.
try the duck/char siew rice at this stall called "bedok cooked food". popiah is not bad too. sadly, there's no good fish soup anymore.
Pfff es super dificil saber que te vas a comer aqui, asi q solo hay q dejarse llevar x el olfato! :)
Chai Ji fish soup is nice
Korean Cuisine at #01-20 avoid! Taste awfully. Cooked by chinaman taste like china food.
#01-05 Mince Meat Fishball Noodle stall serves the best laska with large portion of cockles. Yummeh.
This stall has probably the cheapest priced drinks you can find in Singapore! Small cup (30cents), Big cup (50cents).
